The metal member is held in equilibrium. The member is supported by a square bar fitted through a smooth square hole of the attached collar at point [`A`] and by a roller at point [`B`]. Determine the components of reactions at supports [`A`] and [`B`] considering the load that is applied to the member at point [`C`]. Ignore the mass of the member. Assume that components are positive if they point along the positive axes.


